or", "documentation": ["This module contains the {class}`.Descriptor`, which implements the\nfunctions required by palaestAI-mosaik and, therefore, allows to use\nMIDAS as environment in ARL.\n"], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "midas_palaestrai.descriptor.Descriptor", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "midas_palaestrai.descriptor.Descriptor.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "midas_palaestrai.descriptor.Descriptor.describe", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "params", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Describe the MIDAs scenario.\n\n# Parameters\n\nname\n\n: Name of the scenario to describe.\n\nparams\n\n: A dict containing initial parameters, e.g., parameters\n  normally provided by the command line interface.\n\ncustom_cfg\n\n: A string containing the path to a custom configuration\n  file. This file will be added to the available scenario\n  configurations. To use that specific configuration, make\n  sure to set {attr}`name` accordingly.\n\ninit_path\n\n: A string containing the path to the midas ini file. Default\n  location is used if None is provided.\n\n# Returns\n\ntuple\n\n: A tuple containing a list of sensors and a list of\n  actuators.\n"]}, {"name": "midas_palaestrai.descriptor.Descriptor.get_world", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "params", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Return the world object of the MIDAS scenario.\n\nSee {meth}`describe` for a description of parameters.\n\n# Returns\n\n{obj}`mosaik.scenario.World`\n\n: A fully configured world object that has not started.\n"]}, {"name": "midas_palaestrai.descriptor.Descriptor._configure", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": 